.TH GOBACK 1 "March 2026" "version 1.3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
goback \- scheduled pull-based backup manager for home network services
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B goback
.I command
[\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B goback
is a backup daemon and CLI for pulling backups from home network services.
It supports three backup providers: Home Assistant API backups (WebSocket-based
listing/downloading, REST for triggering, signed URLs for download), SSH/SCP
file transfers, and local command-based backups. Backups are scheduled via cron expressions and managed with
configurable retention policies.
.PP
The daemon runs as a macOS launchd service. Secrets (API tokens, SSH keys)
stored as
.B op://
references are resolved via the 1Password CLI and cached in the platform
keychain (macOS Keychain, Linux secret-tool, Windows cmdkey) using the
.B auth
command, so the daemon runs without requiring 1Password to be unlocked.
SSH configuration is read from
.I ~/.ssh/config
for Host aliases, Hostname, Port, User, and IdentityAgent.
.PP
Configuration is stored in
.I ~/.config/goback/config.yaml
as YAML.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Create a default configuration file at
.IR ~/.config/goback/config.yaml .
Will not overwrite an existing file.
.TP
.B auth
Resolve all
.B op://
secret references in the configuration (API tokens, SSH keys) via the
1Password CLI and cache the resolved values in the platform keychain.
Run this once after changing secrets, before starting the daemon.
.TP
.B auth \-\-clear
Remove all cached secrets from the platform keychain.
.TP
.B clear \fR[\fIname\fR]
Remove cached secrets from the platform keychain. If
.I name
is provided, only secrets for that backup job are removed. Otherwise, all
cached secrets are removed.
.TP
.B completion \fR\fIshell\fR
Output the shell completion script for the given shell. Supported shells:
.BR bash ,
.BR zsh .
.TP
.B daemon
Run the backup scheduler in the foreground. This is the command invoked
by launchd. Schedules all configured backups according to their cron
expressions and runs until interrupted (SIGINT or SIGTERM).
.IP
On startup and every 5 minutes thereafter, the daemon checks for missed
backups by comparing each backup's most recent scheduled fire time against
its last successful run in the status log. This catches backups that were
missed while the Mac was asleep. Missed backups are run sequentially and
logged with a \fBcatchup:\fR prefix. Backups that have never run are
skipped; use \fBgoback run\fR for first-time execution.
.IP
The daemon watches the configuration file for changes and automatically
reloads when it is modified. If the new configuration is invalid, the
previous configuration is kept and a warning is logged. The daemon also
monitors its own binary; when the binary is replaced (e.g., after
\fBmake deploy\fR), the daemon exits so that launchd can restart it with
the new version.
.TP
.B run \fR[\fIname\fR]
Manually trigger a backup. If
.I name
is provided, only that backup job runs. Otherwise, all configured jobs run.
.TP
.B now
Run all configured backups immediately, ignoring schedules. Equivalent to
.BR "goback run" .
.TP
.B dry-run \fR[\fIname\fR]
Simulate backups without transferring files. Connects to each target to
verify connectivity and configuration. For SSH targets, checks that the
remote file exists. For HA API targets, verifies authentication and lists
existing backups on the server. Prints a summary table of results.
.TP
.B list
Display a table of all configured backup jobs showing name, type, folder,
schedule, and retention count.
.TP
.B status
Show recent backup history from the status log, including timestamps,
file sizes, and success/failure status. Displays the most recent 20 entries.
.TP
.B last \fR\fIname\fR
Print the RFC 3339 timestamp of the most recent successful backup for the
named job. Exits with status 1 if no successful backup is found.
.TP
.B version\fR, \fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.TP
.B help\fR, \fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help
Show usage information.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file uses YAML format with two top-level keys:
.TP
.B storage.base_dir
Base directory for all backup files. Supports
.B ~/
expansion.
.TP
.B storage.log_file
Path to the application log file. Supports
.B ~/
expansion.
.TP
.B backups
A list of backup job definitions. Each job supports these fields:
.RS
.TP
.B name
Unique identifier for this backup job (required).
.TP
.B type
Provider type:
.BR ha_api ,
.BR ssh ,
or
.B local
(required).
.TP
.B schedule
Cron expression for when to run (required).
.TP
.B folder
Subdirectory within base_dir for this job's files. Defaults to
.BR name .
.TP
.B filename
Output filename template with Go time format in braces, e.g.
.BR "pihole_backup_{2006-01-02}.zip" .
If omitted, uses
.IR name-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.ext .
.TP
.B retention
Number of backup files to keep. Oldest are deleted first. Default: 4.
.RE
.PP
For
.B ha_api
type, additionally:
.RS
.TP
.B ha_url
Home Assistant base URL (required).
.TP
.B ha_token
Long-lived access token. Supports
.B op://
references for 1Password CLI resolution (required).
.RE
.PP
For
.B ssh
type, additionally:
.RS
.TP
.B host
SSH hostname or alias (required).
.TP
.B user
SSH username (required).
.TP
.B remote_path
Path to the file to download (required unless
.B remote_pattern
is set).
.TP
.B remote_pattern
Glob pattern to find the newest matching file on the remote host (alternative
to
.BR remote_path ).
For example,
.BR "/home/pi/backups/unbound/unbound-*.tar.gz" .
.TP
.B ssh_key
SSH private key for this backup job. Supports
.B op://
references to retrieve keys from 1Password (PKCS#8 format supported).
If omitted, the SSH agent or
.I ~/.ssh/config
IdentityAgent is used.
.TP
.B pre_command
Command to run on the remote host before downloading.
.TP
.B post_command
Command to run on the remote host after downloading.
.RE
.PP
For
.B local
type, additionally:
.RS
.TP
.B local_path
Path to the local file to back up (required unless
.B local_pattern
is set or
.B pre_command
produces a known output file).
.TP
.B local_pattern
Glob pattern to find the newest matching local file (alternative to
.BR local_path ).
.TP
.B pre_command
Command to run locally before copying the file (e.g., to generate the backup).
.TP
.B post_command
Command to run locally after copying the file (e.g., to clean up temp files).
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B goback init
Create a default configuration file with example backup targets.
.TP
.B goback auth
Resolve 1Password secrets and cache them in the system keychain.
.TP
.B goback auth \-\-clear
Remove all cached secrets from the system keychain.
.TP
.B goback clear
Remove all cached secrets from the system keychain.
.TP
.B goback clear homeassistant
Remove only the homeassistant backup's cached secrets.
.TP
.B goback dry-run
Verify connectivity and configuration for all targets without transferring files.
.TP
.B goback dry-run pihole
Test only the pihole backup configuration.
.TP
.B goback run pihole
Manually trigger the pihole backup.
.TP
.B goback now
Run all backups immediately.
.TP
.B goback list
Show all configured backup jobs.
.TP
.B goback status
Show recent backup results.
.TP
.B goback last homeassistant
Print the timestamp of the last successful homeassistant backup.
.TP
.B goback completion zsh > ~/.oh-my-zsh/custom/completions/_goback
Install zsh completions.
.TP
.B eval "$(goback completion bash)"
Enable bash completions for the current session.
.TP
.B goback version
Print version information.
.SH SERVICE MANAGEMENT
To install as a macOS launchd service:
.PP
.RS
.B launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.goback.daemon.plist
.RE
.PP
To stop the service:
.PP
.RS
.B launchctl unload ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.goback.daemon.plist
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred (backup failure, configuration error, or connectivity issue).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/goback/config.yaml
Configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/Library/Logs/goback.log
Default log file location.
.TP
.I ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.goback.daemon.plist
launchd service definition.
